---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="About · patchwaste leaderboard"
      description="Why this leaderboard exists and who runs it.">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-mono tracking-tight mb-6">About</h1>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="font-mono text-lg mb-2">Why this exists</h2>
    <p class="text-mute mb-3">
      In 2024, Enshrouded shipped a 299 KB content change that triggered a 30.6 GB Steam
      download. The studio publicly acknowledged the cause: a single mega-archive that
      contained nearly all game assets had to be resealed for any change inside it.
    </p>
    <p class="text-mute mb-3">
      The Enshrouded pattern is not unusual. It is the default behaviour of most game
      build pipelines. Studios pay for the wasted CDN bandwidth. Players pay for it in
      time, data caps, and shelf space. Nobody pays attention to it because nobody measures it.
    </p>
    <p class="text-mute">
      This leaderboard makes the cost visible.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="font-mono text-lg mb-2">What we do</h2>
    <ul class="text-mute space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
      <li>Catalogue notable patch waste cases with public sources.</li>
      <li>Publish the methodology so anyone can reproduce or challenge a number.</li>
      <li>Update entries weekly as depot manifest verification catches up with the seed list.</li>
      <li>Tag the cause so studios facing the same failure mode can see where to look.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="font-mono text-lg mb-2">What we do not do</h2>
    <ul class="text-mute space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
      <li>Editorial blame. Patch sizes are an engineering artefact, not a moral verdict.</li>
      <li>Closed metrics. Every figure cites a public source.</li>
      <li>Mobile, console-exclusive, or non-Steam titles.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8 border border-line p-6 bg-line/20">
    <h2 class="font-mono text-lg mb-2">The product behind the leaderboard</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-mute mb-3">
      The leaderboard is run by the team behind <strong>patchwaste</strong>, a Rust
      CLI and GitHub Actions gate that catches patch-size regressions in your CI
      pipeline before the patch ships. Built for Unreal and Unity studios.
    </p>
    <a href="https://github.com/pw-labs/patchwaste"
       class="inline-block text-sm font-mono underline hover:text-rust">
      patchwaste on GitHub
    </a>
    <span class="mx-2 text-mute">·</span>
    <a href="/signup/"
       class="inline-block text-sm font-mono underline hover:text-rust">
      Free for indie studios
    </a>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="font-mono text-lg mb-2">Contact</h2>
    <p class="text-mute text-sm">
      Corrections, contributions, and studio queries via the
      <a href="https://github.com/pw-labs/patchwaste" class="underline hover:text-rust">patchwaste repository</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
